title: Save the Date
description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

title: Not So Secret Service
description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

title: Bucketboy!
description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

title: Oh, Daisy!
description: Buttercup is not a fan of Bubbles' newly created digital assistant.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Aspirations
description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

title: A Made Up Story
description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Cat Burglar
description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Hustlecup
description: When Buttercup loses the Professor's latest invention, she'll have to beat The Gangreen Gang at their own game to get it back.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

title: Spider Sense
description: When a monster ruins their relaxing vacation, the Girls run into a familiar face.

title: Super Sweet 6
description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

title: Something's a Ms./Slumbering with the Enemy
description: Something's a Ms: Miss Bellum is acting very strange lately. And she keeps showing up at crime scenes. Has our favorite secretary gone to the dark side, or is there another woman involved here?/Slumbering With The Enemy: When the girls decide to have an all-girl slumber party, a villain decides to crash it. To what lengths will this villain go to keep his identity hidden?

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Rock Off Battle Music Video
description: The Powerpuff Girls rock out!

title: Buttercup vs. Math
description: When Buttercup tests into Honors Math, she tries to avoid being labeled a nerd.

title: Ping Pong Z
description: It's "loser does the dishes" when the girls play ping pong in and around Townsville.

title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

title: Checkin' Out!
description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

title: Find Your Bliss
description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend "Bliss," her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

title: Brainlord
description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

title: Watch It!
description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

title: Rebel Rebel
description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

title: Summer Bummer
description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

title: How to Draw Buttercup
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Buttercup.

title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

title: Poorbucks
description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

title: Blossom3
description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Blossom.

title: Largo
description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

title: Sideline Dad
description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

title: Who's Got the Power?
description: Extended main title is set to music.

title: I'll Be Bake
description: Bubbles and Buttercup's good intentions are bad news for the cake Blossom is trying to bake.

title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

title: The Fog
description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

title: Lights Out!
description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Bubbles.

title: Run, Blossom, Run
description: Blossom oversleeps and she'll stop at nothing to make it to school before she ruins her perfect attendance record!

title: The Oct-Father
description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

title: Mojo the Great
description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

title: How to Draw Bubbles
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Bubbles.

title: Mojo Builds a Shelf
description: Mojo discovers the only thing more difficult than total world domination is DIY furniture.

title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

title: The Spoon
description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

title: Drama Bomb
description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

title: Brain Freeze
description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

title: Our Brand is Chaos
description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

title: Tagalong
description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.
